{"word":"κτητός","slug":"κτητός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κτητός</b></el> <el>(κτητός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <a href='S:κτάομαι'><el>κτάομαι</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>that may be gotten</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>worth getting, desirable</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>acquired</i>: <el>κτητή</el> <i>a female slave</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}